The paper deals with the application of deep convolutional neural networks (CNN) and compressed sensing (CS) for cell detection and localization in microscopy images. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), which deals with image processing and analysis. The paper also discusses the backpropagation rule for training algorithms that implement a sparse code recovery layer, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE). Finally, the paper deals with microscopy images, which could also fall under the category of multimedia (cs.MM).
